

Idris "Alex" Ughiovhe (born 27 January, 1983 in Washington DC) is an American footballer currently playing for Crystal Palace Baltimore. He can play at right back, central defence or in defensive midfield.

From 2002 until 2005 Alex played for and was captain of the Howard University Bison, and for Richmond Kickers Future in the USL Premier Development League, prior to being selected by Chicago Fire in the 2006 MLS SuperDraft. In 2006 Alex played reserve matches for both Chicago Fire and DC United, but was not signed to a full contract by either team. He signed for Crystal Palace Baltimore in 2007.

